            <Image src={EPDmockupIMG} alt='Preview of an EPD' class='w-100' />

            <figcaption
              class='position-absolute bottom-25px left-25px w-250px border-radius-4px bg-white d-flex align-items-center pt-20px pb-20px ps-25px pe-25px'
              data-anime='{ "translateY": [50, 0], "opacity": [0,1], "duration": 800, "delay": 1200, "staggervalue": 100, "easing": "easeOutQuad" }'
            >
              <h2
                class='text-dark-gray fw-700 ls-minus-3px sm-ls-minus-2px vertical-counter d-inline-flex mb-0 text-nowrap border-end border-1 border-color-extra-medium-gray pe-20px me-20px'
                data-to='50'
              >
              </h2>
              <span class='text-dark-gray lh-22 fw-500 d-inline-block'
                >Projects completed</span
              >
            </figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
        <div
          class='col-xl-5 offset-xl-1 col-lg-6 col-md-9'
          data-anime='{ "el": "childs", "translateY": [50, 0], "opacity": [0,1], "duration": 600, "delay": 0, "staggervalue": 100, "easing": "easeOutQuad" }'
        >
          <h2 class='fw-600 text-dark-gray ls-minus-2px'>
            How is an EPD different from LCA?
          </h2>
          <p class='w-90 lg-w-100 md-mx-auto mb-35px'>
            An Environmental Product Declaration (EPD) is an LCA study but with
            additional requirements for third party verification. An EPD is a
            standardized and transparent method for assessing and reporting the
            environmental impacts associated with the production of a product.
            It encompasses all relevant mandatory and/or optional stages of a
            product's life cycle, from raw material extraction to disposal.
          </p>
          <!-- <p class='w-90 lg-w-100 md-mx-auto mb-35px'>
            Type III EPDs which comply with EN 15804:2012+A2:2019 and EN ISO
            14025 standards meet the requirements of green building
            certification systems such as LEED v4, BREEAM International NC 2016,
            and BREEAM v6 and others.
          </p> -->


